entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="mex" o="La carcelera de mi mujer me pidió que gorroneara un filtro de aire, como si tuviera edis de sobra tirados por ahí." t="The ol' ball and chain told me to scrounge up an air filter. Like I got the eds just lyin' around somewhere." b="" a=""/>

<kiroshi l="mex" o="Además, ¿para qué chingados necesito un filtro? Se va a tapar a la primera tormenta que azote." t="Besides... What in the hell do I need a filter for? First good storm and it'll clog right up." b="" a=""/>
I could give you one. For free, too. Bulldozers razed my trailer yesterday... But goddamn, if that filter didn't make it through in one piece.
<kiroshi l="mex" o="Ah, chingao. ¿Qué pasó?" t="Oh, shit. What happened?" b="" a=""/>
Ehh, got up to my ears in debt, ended up losing the house. But then they said the ground might actually be worth more.
<kiroshi l="mex" o="Güey, eso... es una pinche mierda." t="Man, that is... That is fucked up." b="" a=""/>
Yeah, I dunno. First time for months I'm not worried about another eviction notice, at least.
I haven't felt this free in... I dunno how long.
